{
    "action": "Final Answer",
    "action_input": "Code-switch speech synthesis refers to the ability of a speech synthesis system to seamlessly switch between languages or dialects within a single utterance. It's particularly useful in multilingual societies where individuals commonly speak more than one language and may switch mid-sentence. To teach such synthesis, one must consider the phonetic and prosodic properties of each language involved, ensure the synthesized voice can produce accurate sounds from both languages, and handle the linguistic context that governs code-switching patterns. Machine learning models for this purpose are often trained on bilingual speech datasets. The key is the ability of the system to recognize the switch points and produce natural-sounding speech in both languages, maintaining coherence and context."
}
