{
    "action": "Final Answer",
    "action_input": "Code-switch speech synthesis is a technology that enables a synthetic voice to alternate between different languages or dialects within a single dialogue or sentence. This is particularly useful in multilingual contexts where speakers may naturally mix languages. When creating a code-switched speech system, several factors need to be addressed such as accurate pronunciation of words from different languages, language detection to switch between corresponding text-to-speech engines, and proper intonation for naturalness. Training code-switch speech synthesis systems typically involves using machine learning models and substantial bilingual or multilingual speech datasets to teach the system the nuances of each language, including when and how speakers switch between them. The goal is to enable smooth transitions without losing the context or meaning of the spoken message."
}
